# GitHub Pages - Disable Jekyll processing
# This file should be renamed to .nojekyll after upload
# Created on 2026-03-17

# Purpose:
# This file disables GitHub Pages' Jekyll processing, ensuring that
# HTML files are served directly without Jekyll transformation.

# Instructions:
# 1. Upload this file to your GitHub repository
# 2. Rename it to ".nojekyll" (without quotes)
# 3. Commit the change

# Why .nojekyll is needed:
# - GitHub Pages uses Jekyll by default
# - Jekyll may interfere with HTML file serving
# - .nojekyll tells GitHub to skip Jekyll processing
# - Ensures privacy-policy.html and service-agreement.html work correctly
